\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid397911 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Lily. Mrs Lily Lee. Lily Lee. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 10, Ilkley Road, Riddlesden, Keighley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And you are a widow now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Now I am, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And the year when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 1890.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And the place where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Normanton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember how long you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, about four years. About four years. I'd just started school. We used to start at three. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So you moved when you were four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In Normanton just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In the same district was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, Altofts. Altofts. Just a little place. Me father was on a railway and he went into a railway house you see. Altofts. Just a village, just out of Normanton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But you were actually born in Normanton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. In Normanton, in the parish, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it because of your father's work that you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. He was on the railway and he got a rail - you see, they just lived in a cottage, yo
u know, they were married - just lived in a cottage. And then he got a railway house that they - bigger you see. He was on the railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you move again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not for years, not 'til I was about - eleven. Then we went back to Normanton. To a bigger house, a bit gibger and better house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it in the same district of Normanton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 As you first came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We lived in that house about two years and then mother mov
ed to another one and she was in it - oh - how long would we be in the other house then, about twenty-two years I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Why was it that your mother moved then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Better house you see. Yes. And bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your father was still alive wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Just two of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And your sister is younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Two years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Approximately - twenty-three. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your mother was twenty-two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. He'd be twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well he - he - well from two year old I was at Normanton, but he came from Staffordshire. Well he was - small, a baby, two years old and - in that time
 there was a big slump in - near Wolverhapston it was where he - Dudley, not Didley, Oldbury, near Wolverhampton, somewhere down there, well there was a big slump and in Normanton then there was building new collieries. And you know like they're moving no
w, they had to move - people had to move with the work. And that's how his father came to Normanton, it's a mining area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your grandfather was a miner was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. And they moved them me father was two years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What was your father's occupation, he worked on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 On the railways, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What exactly did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 He was a - went they called in them days a plate-layer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he have any other job either before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. No. He never worked in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he ever do any casual or part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. He just worked normal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, they were all out of work at fiftieth slump. They had to - sign - you know before the war there was a big 
- you know, before the 1914 war there was some dreadful times for them. And he had to - get casual work, you know. And so - well he worked part time sometimes on the - for the gas company. Or where they could get work they had to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Labouring sort of jobs would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, yes, they had to do. Yes. Were out of work when he were fifty. That was slump, you know, no work for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's the only occasion is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did it go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh fairly long time, it was a lot of slack work you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you mean several months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, yes, well - well - he never did really get a proper regular job again, not regular. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of work did he do after that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well just labouring, where he could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 He didn't go back to the railway at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Wakefield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Had she any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, she worked for a tailoring - tailoress. But you see they were young when they got married in them - days, weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she work as all after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. Oh they didn't used to go to work when they were married. Well there wasn't work for then like there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you were a child you lived for four years at normanton and then you went to this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So that the bulk of your childhood was spent at the village?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, it was. Yes. We'd a long way to walk to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You were in the one house in this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember how many rooms there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. We'd a - we'd a nice living room and a kitchen and two bedrooms. Well they were nice houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did anybody else besides your parents and you and your sister live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You hadn't any other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. They hadn't money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. All done at home, everything done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, mother made them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 For your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. She used to make his shirts and pyjams and - you know, all that sort of thing. House sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were any clothes at all bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No, everything mother made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well you just had to get them when you - you had to make them last as long as you could. Hand 'em down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you have a pair of new shoes bought for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. From me mother and father yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Then when they were too small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Too small they'd go down to her, then she got bigger than me then and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Then did the process operate in reverse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's it. Yes, you often wonder how they did - and she used to keep hers lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where would she go to to buy your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well I don't - I couldn't tell you, only in the shop. Woodman's in the town, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That would be in Normanton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Oh you didn't go out of town to shop. A nice little shopping places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, oh - did his share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - ordinary you know. Helped to wash up and - I suppose he would 'til we got big enough and then he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he do any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would he make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that his regular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Decorating or repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. They had to do it you see in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Repairs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about improvements to the house, did he do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No, because the firm did it you see. The railway. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he do anything for you as small children, like dressing or undressing or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, I can't remember that but I don't thing he would, no. Mother was young you know, she - she did most of it for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, we had a good home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not often, they all - we all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would your father look after you while your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. There was no - nowhere to go out to much, they didn't go out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any tasks to carry out regularly at home to you're your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, when we got old enough. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of jobs did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well, you know, the washing up and - washing the kitchen floor and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have specific jobs assigned to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You just helped with anything that needed doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Helped in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did you continue to do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well until we went to work you know and their - you see I went most of the girls in Normanton went out to service, you know, but - my mot
her and dad tried to bring us up to try to to the best they could for us and they put me to a trade. And we had to go two years then for nothing you know. Apprenticed. Which was a big sacrifice - from fourteen to sixteen. I never earnt anything you see. N
o, so - but - I hadn't been - long before I had to try and make - help to make our clothes - before I really learned.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you stop doing the jobs in the house when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I had to, when I went sewing. I've always been a sew-er.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you as the - older sister help your younger sister to do things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do things, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - I should have to show her how to do things I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, I've helped with everything, yes. Little mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your younger sister help you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A bit. She wasn't just the same type was you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother or your father put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Mother. Usually. Oh but they never left us, there was - no leaving children in them days. No babysitters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How old were you when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh about eleven I should think, ten or eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you share the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The two sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your mother and father had the other bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The other bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You didn't have a bathroom in that house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. No. Never heard of them. We used to have a big bath and put the set pot on. Big tin. On a Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was this in the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In the kitchen. Set the copper on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you have clean clothes to put on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Underclothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That would follow on from your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bath; every week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In - it was the living room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there ever any occasions when you ate in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In the living room, it was an oven, you know, range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You didn't have any other sort of cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. There were no gas cookers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well about eight o'clock you know before we went to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Which members of the family were present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Just - us three 'cos - dad went out by half past five in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did he manage for his meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Mother used to take them. Packed up then he used to come home in the evening and have an evening meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would he get his breakfast himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, he'd take it you see. They just have a cup of tea and then go. Then - used to pack a basket you know. Until he came home in the evening, then - mother cooked then for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 For the three of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, we had - we had ours at lunchtime. We had our dinner at 1 - when we come from school, at twelve, and then mother used to make his at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of a meal did you have for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well in those days it used to be a bit of toast and marmalade, you know, and there weren't flakes. Porridge very often. And tracle, you know, bread and treacle. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have a different breakfast on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bacon - a bit of bacon. Oh we were all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your midday meal was a cooked meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of a meal did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh well, they used to do different things you know. Used to get a joint for the we
ekend and then it used to be hashed up and - cold one day and hashed up and then she used to make broth and - Yorkshire pudding and, you know, what we used to call spotty dick. Suet pudding. Yes, we had some good meals you know. Yes, we were well looked a
fter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have a drink at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. We'd rice pudding or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You always had the two courses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Always - yes, yes, yes. Yes, we always had a good - oh well, to say the money, me dad got eighteen shillings a week. So you can tell.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Usually a bit of jam, sometimes - now again we got a boiled egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 During the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 During the week. And on a Saturday well it used to be sometimes a - a feast, a bit of a feast, we'd have a tin of something you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Some sort of meat or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes, well, no, there wasn't tinned meat, it was - I've forgotten now what - what we used to have, what we used to like. Was it prawns? Yes. And fruit - we had a lot of fruit - that was going. A banana, you know, or an apple. Or an orange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about Sunday tea, was that special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh yes, we always had special - something a little bit special on the Sunday. Well it used to go generally hot but scones, stewed plums, stewed rhubarb, stewell you know, everything that they cold stew. Fruit and custard we'll say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you have tea to drink again at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any sort of supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. We - used to generally have some milk or - and a biscuit, something like that. Drink of milk you know and some biscuits, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Mother baked everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she make jam?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bottle, pickles, yes, all the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she do anything with vegetables, preserving vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was any wine made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Or beer brewed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. Never. No. Me grandma used to do this nettle beer but she didn't. Pop - we used to call it - I've forgot what we called it now - it had a name hadn't it what we used t
o have at grandma's, that nettle beer she used to make. Not pop, but we used to like it. Fizzy, it were fizzy. Made from nettle you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you often have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Me granny used to make it. And we liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was any medicine made for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Not much. You didn't have much medicine, no. Brimstone and tracle. And - what were that other - brimstone and treacle in spring, in the mornings, spoonful. And then - what were that other - hated it. Used to have it about once a week. Br
own - brown stuff. Oh I've forgotten now what we call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father or mother grow any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, they hadn't a garden. Not a big garden. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Off a greengrocer. Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that a greengrocer who came round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Used to come every week and used to sell oranges seven for threepence. She used to buy seven every week and we had to have them cut in half. And they last all week 'til he come again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What else did she buy from him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bananas you know, and pass - anything that were going. We had plenty of grens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she buy any tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not very often. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, not - no, we didn't just have it much then. It - it were all stewed fruits you know. What - what was in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say they hadn't got a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. But there was people around had allotments and they were - in those days used to be very neighbourly and they used to have a lot goven. Po
p a cabbage on the wall, you know. You know, they were really good. Lots were that had these big allotments. But me dad was never a - a gafen man. And he wasn't - he didn't take any allotment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 They didn't keep any livestock of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have meat fairly often during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. Once a week, you know, when she'd go to the butchers. On a Saturday night. All shopping was done on a Saturday. 'Cos they didn't used to get their wages while Saturday dinner. Then you went int
o Normanton and did all the shopping. And bought the meat and - for the week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What would she buy in the way of meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well usually a roast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That would be it would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That would be - oh that were it - and some stewing meat. For pies. Yes. And it lasted the week you know, it had to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that bought in Normanton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. This greengrocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you know anybody who did any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Any poach? No. No, not round there - no. Suppose there would be a few that would do. But I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember seeing your mother having less of anything to eat so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I have. Thought about it since. 
And heard her say, well I don't think I want any. But - she would - it were because there wouldn't be any. You don't think of it at the time though do you. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things would that be, anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Anything, yes, anything special you see.
 Like if the fruit wouldn't go all round she'd be the one that wouldn't - she'd say, well I don't think I'll have any, you know. 'Cos as you're growing up you want more don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. He wasn't a big - no, no. They always saw that we had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you allowed to talk during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not much. Not like they do now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But you could speak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, yes, free. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We had to have what it was. What was there we had to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We didn't leave any. No. Mother just used to seem to know just - what we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we'd have it you see, ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. We had a very free home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, if there was any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Properly. I never remember when we didn't do. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about the way you sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh we had to sit up straight and - mind our manners. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. No. Not at meal times no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When we'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Please may I leave the table. Thank you for a good tea. Yes. Yes, said grace at beginning in our turn. I don't know whe
ther it was in turn or one one week and one other. Oh yes, we had to ask properly to leave the table. There were no - we weren't allowed to run round with a piece of bread in us hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You all sat at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How was the meal served, was it your mother who dished it out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What order would she serve you in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Pudding firs, yorkshire you know. Then the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The pudding on its own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And then your vegetables course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Veggies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who would she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well who she would serve first would be dad if he was there. But if not, either of us, whichever were nearest, it didn't matter. She used to serve us all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And herself last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Last. Then we all started together you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember when your sister was younger, when she was very tine, how old she'd been she would come up to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, I can remember right well them sitting her up to table. Out of high chair. She'd be about two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What happened before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 She used to be in a - tall chair you know. And then she started having a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it your mother who fed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. She could feed herself but I could feed her a bit. Oh I can remember little bits of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Oh she was very well - she'd been very well brought up. She really married beneath her a bit if you - if you know what I mean - she l
ived differently brought up but - she liked me dad and she had him and - that was it. She went to a private school and she'd had a very god bringing up. In Wakefield. So she was very good mannered. You see. Folk used to say she was ladylike you know and -
 even though she hadn't much to go on with she - she saw that we were properly brought up you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was she an affectionate sort of mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Very much. Just forty years since she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If you had any worries when you were a child could you talk to your mother about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your father, was he easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. easy. Easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Easy going you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. He used to play on he rug and - play all sorts with us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you talk to him if you were worried about things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Yes, we were very fortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh well, they expected to be - us to be - proper and we did do. Respected them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your younger sister in any certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - if she was naughty I could tell them you know or - but we weren't left much on our o
wn so - I didn't really have much to do with her you know, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Stick up for yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well, they hoped we should grow up to be good citizens, good christians, and went to Sunday school and we were taught right from being born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, very much. Very m
uch. Especially personal things you know. You know, you're - you're attitude to - well, we'll say to sex as it is now, we were brought up very - you know - we had to know right from wrong very young. Taught to, me mother did. Clean living - clean - sex - 
yes, clean living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Terrible. We never heard it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When grown ups were talking could you join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. You had to shut up. Kids chip in now don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - we'd get - you - you'd get a good smack bottom. They used to smack your bottom in them days. I tell ours that's what they want now and again and they ask me what that means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who would punish you, your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Mother. Mother - never dad. He never touched us. Never. No. He was easier. Because he wasn't with you all day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things would your mother punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well being cheaky you know, shipping in. Anyt
hing you did wrong. I never remember really doing anything every wrong. No. We weren't anges but - you'd come home perhaps with some torn clothes or somebody'd been fighting or something. Then she'd want to know all - how it happened and - you'd perhaps o
et one when you got home, a good smack you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Not - not to well on it, no. Not with fear. No. We were never afraid.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember how you felt when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, you were very upset. You didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh from me parents, from home life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 From both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Both of them - both. Both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did either of them play a more important part than the other do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. We didn't have a lot but - it were different you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Only new - little bit of something from them you know. There wasn't birthday cards and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have something special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. A cake, perhaps iced a bit. But it wouldn't be a fruit cake, it'd be just a sponge cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Candles on. Yes. Yes. Little friends. Little teaparties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that the regular thing when it was your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. When it was a birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes, we used to have a lovely Christmas Day. You know, trim up and - trim the house up and we used to have to make - we used to make our own trimmings though. We used to make a lot of paper flowers, daffodils, you know, and all that kind of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How would you actually spend the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well we used to - we had and auntie that lived at - about three miles away and we always went there for Christmas, to my mother's sister. Every Christmas. And it was about a three mil
e walk, we had to walk it. And that's all I remember of Christmas when we were children. We always went to this auntie. Oh yes, at home yes. But you said Christmas day. Oh yes, we hung our stockings up and got mixed things in there. Then we always went fo
r
 Christmas to me aunt. Hated it as well. Yes. Because they were right well off and we always had to behave that much well it spoilt it. We were always glad to come home. When you look back now - I didn't think at time what it was but - you do when you get
 older, you look back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 It was the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. They had a trap and a horse and a big house and - and me mum and dad hadn't much you know and - and I used to feel right - as I got a little bit older, eleven, you know, you began to feel then what it
 was you know. And we had to behave that much didn't we, that it spoilt all the joy of - and they just had one boy and he was two years older than me. And - ruined he was you know. And - when you look back, I used to say her, haven't we had some miserable
 Christmasses. But we had to go you know because me grandma was there, it was a family - they used to do you know, like family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, me dad was in a band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You know, brass band. Everybody used to get fed up with this thing and we used to put balls of wool in, so it didn't make a noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That was the only one was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And it was just your father who played it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Then when we went to Sunday school we got the anniversary hymns. We got the music, was thrilled because he could play them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he used to practice at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. With this thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 It was a trumpet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. You know - trem something I don't know - I can remember. I
t was the railway band he was in. Yes. Yes. And of course he had to practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well I sang a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 As a child was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Yes, as a child, yes. Used to go round with him to - sing sometimes for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You mean you sang solos?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Little hymns you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you make music together at home as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well as we got a bit older and we got on a little bit better we got working we got a piano and I learned then, we learnt
 then. But that had to wait while we got older, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say your father used to play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A lot. A lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. You know, snap and - you know, we used to play snap cards and - table games, dominoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we used to play outside. Pies ball and - cricket or anything we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we used to go out and play in the back, yes, in the garden. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh yes. Mother was a big reader. She used to sit and read a lot to us at night. All these good books, Coral Island and - and, you know, the books that children - Uncle Tom's Cabin. Well we couldn't read them, she used to read them to us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, not much, he only used to read the paper. And they only got one once a week, a paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that a local paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, there was no money for - anything like that, not 'til we grew up a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents read aloud to each other at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. They were both readers - read to themselves. I suppose they would after we'd gone to bed. Me mother was in the library. She was a big reader. Oh and she had a lot of good books of her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. Only me - grandma when I was eighteen. Oh yes, we had a baby. A brother. Yes. Yes, I was seven. And he died at five month. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember anything much about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Yes, remember going in this - cab and putting little cot under the driver's seat. Always seemed to well on my mind that. Cabby man was us here then there was a place for a little coffin in the front of the - - it was horsedri
ven thing and - I can remember - I can remember as vivid an anything, it was a little coffin, you know. Ooh it did stand out in your memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there just the one cab?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's all, with me father and mother in and us two, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did anybody else attend the funeral at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Only grandma. I were only seven though you see, but it dwelt on my mind a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about mourning?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, they put you in black. Used to put you in black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You were put in black for your little brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, no, I don't think we were for - but we were for me grandma, and that wasn't long after. Yes, about a year after. Yes. They used to put children in black
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did it go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A matter of weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember your grandmother's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that a bigger affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Well - me father's parents, remember both them. But me mother's mother - I was eighteen so - well I was grown up when she died.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you in mourning for six months for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Right up to 1914 war people went in mourning as - after the war when things changed you know. They don't do - that now. They didn't do it after the - war was over. Things completely changed, it were like another world. Yes, it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 As a child were you taken out to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not in Normington - we used to go to Wakefield, to me mother's friends. She had two or three friends and we used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh about - see me father couldn't - they could get a pass on the railway you see and we could go and we used to go about - oh once in two or three weeks to see me mother's different friends, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, always. On a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Sometimes. He'd take us for a walk. Because it was all friends you know, in the country. But we usually all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember any other sort of outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Never at Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Not until we got a bit older and then they took us to - Leeds. To Roundworth Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. We once went to Bournemouth with - then we went to Bridlington quite a lot didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You went pretty frequently did you, each year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 To Bridlington. No, not every year. No. About - once in two years perhaps. You'd to save up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes. Right up to being - you know, as we got old enough to go with friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you go for a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, just one week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well just - well - all we did play on the sands that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 They 
did - sit on the sands. You know, take a rug and sit on the sand, well they wouldn't - they hadn't a right lot of money you see, you didn't - you just got your - well we always had holiday we'd just to sit and play Like you did at home but it were seaside
. But you know, we used to get better weather. Somehow, I don't know why but - you didn't used to have all this wet in summer. We've often said after 1914 war the weather broke.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you stay in a boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Kept to ourselves you know, they used to do. Mother used to take everything with her, all the bread baked and everything you know. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she look after that side of it while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. While we were there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Or did the landlady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, not the la
ndlady. No. The landlady did the cooking. But we used to have a little table where we used to go to cut up the bread and - you know, they used to do that. It was only way people got in their station of life got a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you spend Saturdays as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - playing out you know. - In the the house when it was winter. Nothing special on a Saturday. Only this, going into town at - after tea, shopping. If you wanted anything new it were lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 New to wear you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Bits of material for mother to make up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How often did you get new clothes like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well anniversary. Sunday school anniversary. That's all, once a year. Then you had to have them - you - your Sunday clothes you used to have to wear on a Saturday. All Sunday clothes had to go away then you know at Sunday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you spend your Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well we went to Sunday school. Yes. We were big Methodists you know then. Well we are still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you play games at all on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. We - not even have a dolly out. No, right strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents think that it was wrong to .....?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do anything on a Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 To work or to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Read. 'Course us Sundays used to be taken up because - wer were far
 away from Sunday school and we'd to walk there in the morning, come back for dinner and go back in afternoon. So Sunday was soon gone. There was only really Sunday evening - 'cos we didn't go to chapel at night until we got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they didn't go a right lot. They went sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 At night do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 At night, and took us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, they didn't go in the morning. See me dad had to get up early every other morning. And me m
other cooked on a Sunday, cooked the Sunday dinner. You know, the traditional Sunday dinner. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But you went regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there any Sunday school outings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Not taking away though, we used to have a - what
 they call a school treat, and a but you know, bag with a bun in and - given in the fields you know, and a pot of tea. It were a big field - they didn't used to take them off like they do now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You had your field day once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Field day once a year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What other social activities did the chapel organise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well, as we got older there was plenty. As we got older, there was what we used to call Christian Endeavour and - Band of Hope and - there was something - choir practice when 
we got big enough, old enough. But you see you get to fourteen before you can go to - those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you belong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we went in everything when we got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did the choir have any outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we usually had a trap every year in a wagonette. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that a fairly short distance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, just outside Pontefract we used to go, Brockenhill Woods. In a wagonette.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Always to the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, because it wasn't so far. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You belonged to the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did it do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - they used to talk to you you know and used to sing hymns and - and have cinematograph you know. It was like a social - little - it - as you might say a social club. Active - very active.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And what about the Christian Endeavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well that was more - a topic. You learnt a lot there. They - they did a topic you see but you'd to be - you're a bit older before you go there. And then you learnt to speak and - and ask questions you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no, we didn't belong anything else, no. Not 'til we got older and then we were in amateurs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You said grace at meal times, were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not downstairs no. Just - we just said our prayers when we went to bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Not particularly. No. But he did take a big 
interest in - the adult school. He had a lot to do with that. Quakers. Quite a big worker for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 For the Quakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well the adult school you know and it's a section of it. It's the same idea. They used to meet on a Sunday morning at nine o'clo
ck. Did the adult school. And he went there rather than chapel. For the men it was, men. Adult school. They had a - they built there own place. We had our wedding reception in it. They built their own - you know, they had their own place. In Normanton, it
 
was a big thing. They were the big tradesmen that started it. And my - me dad was a big worker for it, he liked it. It was a Quaker idea, they could sit you know and chat and - well the Quakers don't sit and chatter do they, they're quiet but - I mean to 
s
ay, was - it wasn't - it was very informal. They could light their pine you know and listen to the topic you know. It was a free - more freer, you know, and he loved it. And it was with him when he used to go to Castleton visiting when I used to - he used
 to take me to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was this Adult School completely independant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Of any particular church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. YES. Yes. It's - it is - it is a - an organisation. They have them all over. They've a lovely place at - have you - do you
 know this country, near Mallom. You know, they have hostels. For the young people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your father actually worked for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Very hard. Yes. Had a big - used to have a big picture of him up, he liked it. It was the work he liked. But we was getting
 older then you know. He didn't go out when wer were little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things did he do for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well he - he used to do the books and used to - go round visiting and - sick and - and organise for the speaker you know to come. Worked hard for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 He was the secretary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 YES. But that was after we grew up a bit you see. Yes, Cadburys and Rowntrees.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were they associated with this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 With it - with it. And do you know who - my mother and dad once entertained? Gandhi. Now that's 
a big thing isn't to say. Gandhi. He was at the university. And that was before the war you know. He was at Leeds University, a student, and everybody was boycotting him you know 'cos of his principles you know. He'd been to prison. Oh he had a hectic lif
e
 had Gandhi. And he came to speak for - me dad got him to speak at the Adult School in Normanton and - I - I'll never forget, and - and he said to me mother he were bringing him. She said, you're never bringing that fellow here for tea? And they did do. A
nd he had his tea with me mother and dad. And look what he got to be. Gandhi. You never know do you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you actually meet him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 YES. Yes. Yes, so he - they entertained - that was all through adult school you see. He'd - oh my dad were full o
f him. He said, that man'll get on. But oooh you know he did have a rough time you know before he got to be what he did get to be. When I told somebody once that he'd been in my - my mother and dad's they couldn't believe it. He was at university at Leeds
.
 And that was through Adult - School. YES? Contact you see. He had his tea with them. That was an experience we never forgot. Surprising isn't it the contacts you make like that. Specially when you've read all about him and heard all about him and - me mo
ther said, I don't want him in my house, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did she respond when he came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
She did do - she make his tea. 'Cos everybody was agen him at that time you know, and he was a - you know, was agitator and - I can't remember a right lot about 
it but I know there was a lot of - you'll only have read about it - talk about it at that time. Don't remember a lot about - but I know after that you know and he went back to his own country he did a lot of good. Yes. He got a very good religious backgro
und you know at Leeds. Through the Adult School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say your father wasn't interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Not political. He was a big Liberal if he was - if you asked him what he was you know. Lloyd George's man you know. Yes. At that time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you know why he held that view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. I don't because we never - we never talked politics. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, she never bothered. She was a Liberal if she was anything. Because me grandma was a bit - Gladstone - big photograph 
enlarged of Gladstone. He was a big Liberal you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Are you talking about your father's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. My mother's. So - we were - background's Liberal. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember your father and mother voting in an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes. We used to have - we used to have to wear a big yellow rosette. Used to see that we had one on as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Even though you were too young to vote yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. We went to school with these big yellow - and some of them were there with blue one
s you know. I can remember that right well. Fighting in playground. Yellow bellies they used to call us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In some places at that time people felt they might lose their job or their house if they voted differently from their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes the
y did. Oh well it didn't make any difference where me dad worked you see, no. Oh they used to do in - I know, in business, yes, it did. I married into a big Tory family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father work for the Liberal party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Nothing. Never did a
nything. He wasn't a politician at all. Only - only I - we know he was a Liberal. And we had to - used to - mother used to make us these yellow ribbons. Oh he was a Methodist yes. He was a Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they never had any spare time much. Mother was sewing you know and - me dad mending shoes or - you know, they had to do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, she'd chapel you know, she 
used to go to the women's meeting. And - as - sewing. They started a women's section and she went a bit. But she liked chapel you know, she used to go to sewing meetings, she used to do some lovely work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she ever go out just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, she used to go once a year to a ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your mother and father was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What special occasion was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh it was the - Druids Ball they called it. That were her special - once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who organised that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well a
 club you see. Like Oddfellowes is a club and - was some sort of society, I can't remember much about it but - it were a big day, that were the only evening out we ever had. Used to have a new blouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 For the ball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When did your father get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh about six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh - every - they never went out at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father ever attend any club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he ever go to a pub at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And your mother wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Just this band. Used to take his time with band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 He didn't attend races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about betting?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father or mother belong to any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well when the war was on they started those - that saving club then you know, for the war. They start - they were in that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about sixtness or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes, they were in a - Druids, this club. That were the only thing they were ever in. Yes. And insurance, they used to pay insurance you know. About - penny a week you know. Stunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you get on with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh we used to fight a bit sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Mostly with her 'til we got older and then we had some friends then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you play with neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, plenty of children. Friendly, all about, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Outside in the gardens. Yard - we had a good yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you play in the street at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Weren't in the streets. We had us own back yard you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you play in the other childrens' homes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not much. They didn't used to do that, not like they do now. Everybody had enough with their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well we used to play piesball and - rounders, as they cal it, and hopscotch, checks. You never see them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, was - used to enjoy ourselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Could you play with anybody you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there some children that your parents would discourage you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. We - we did very well where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you belong to any youth organization-?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, because there weren't such things then until we got a bit older and then there was youth at chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you were still at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, because you see - yes, I liked sewing you know, before I was put to it I liked it. Dressing dollies and - you know, I liked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. Well I used to like going collecting - down by
 the river, snakes and sanails and all sorts but I used to have to - have to go back and throw them back in. Oh most children do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You went for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We did a bit of tennis when we got a bit bigger yo
u know but - from Sunday school - but you see, that's when you're coming on a bit bigger. We never sort of - did anything 'til we were about thirteen, you know. You were kept up more quieter, you know, just went out with your parents. 'Til you was about -
 'til we were about thirteen, then we started going out with friends a bit. And then it was Sunday school. Things that were going in there. Then as you got still a bit older went in the amateurs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That was after you'd started to work was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. You - you start then to live. Start making your own friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 While you were still at school you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you bicycling at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Well I didn't have a bike 'til I was about sixteen. No. You - you see, you didn't
 - you see love, you had to get grown up a bit before you could - you - not like the children now with their little bikes, we hadn't little bikes. We had to wait 'til we grow up a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you take part in any sports as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Only at Sunday school. Races. Yes. Three-legged races and - all the races that they do now. But it was only a Sunday school sports day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 While you were still at school did you ever go to a theatre or a concert or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. No. No. No, properly grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Penny a week - ha'penny a week and then got to a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. When we were children. Used to take a bit of spending on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh - aniseed balls and - anything that you got a lot for your money. Take a bit of spending. And of course as we got a bit older we were taken to pantomime at Leeds. But that's when you're coming on a bit, a bit older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If she was ill, do you remember her being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh me grandma. She lived at Wakefield, she used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you remember what happened when your sister was born or your small brother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, I can remember me grandma was there that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents have any relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, me mother - me father's side was near. His sisters and brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not my - yes. But not a lot because they were - a fair distance off you know. And you didn't get out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What do you mean by a fair distance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well, a good walk. Like from here to Keighley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A couple of miles or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes. We weren't near one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You mentioned your mother having friends in Wakefield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, all her friends were in Wakefield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your father have friends as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, visit them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh only me - me father ha
dn't any particular friends, only - that he made you know at work and the Adult School but they didn't used to visit in them days. Well because they couldn't entertain, you know. Everybody was alike. You know, they hadn't the money. They couldn't - they c
ouldn't do as they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents share the same friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Oh yes, me dad didn't have separate friends, no. Couples you know, that were friendly with. Oh yes, they'd some very nice friends.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Apart from your mothergoing to Wakefield to see her friends, where did your parents see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
At home. They'd call at home to our house. But we didn't have a lot of callers. Somehow it was - different world altogether. Quieter. Before the war, and that seemed to alter things because people started mixing more. After the 1914 war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 After it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. When - when it was on you know. You see, people got going about mixing more. But before that everything was very quiet really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember friends being invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, they'd tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would they be invited to come for their tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 For their tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 On particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh it'd be Sunday you know. 'Cos it's the only day they used to be free you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you say that the friends invited in were our mother's friends or your father's friends or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they call in casually without an invitation at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not very often. No, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh they were friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they come in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not much. Me mother wasn't one that went in and out of folks' houses. They'd chatter outside a bit. But - she hadn't fo
lks coming in and out, she was - quieter. But very neighbourly, she'd go anywhere if anybody wanted anything. And do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 To help neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Yes, she would. But as a regular thing I never remember anybody coming in and out. We were very quietly brought up really.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 People say that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well often wondered what they did. Well you see 
we'd be in bed when we were young, and of course as we got older we were out. And then they started going about with couples of their own age you know. You see, they'd only be young, they were married young and had us young you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of things do you think they would do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - they would go for walks you see. And - or else it'd be something at chapel. Or something at Adult Aschool. We used to have social evenings at the Adult School and dances. And me mother and father liked dancing. Y
es, and they used to go to the church. You know, the - church used to run social evenings. You know, dances. And they used to love dancing, both of them were good dancers, very good dancers. And that was their main interest. Used to go to the social eveni
ngs at the church. You see, the chapels didn't have dancing. But they both liked dancing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they go when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, if me grandma was over. To look, after u-.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did she come quite often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. She was a widow. Yes. 
That was me dad and mother's only - hobby. They used to love a bit of dancing. At church. These church socials. They used to do a lot in - village churches then, the church a hall. You know, in the village church halls, they used to do a lot of that. What
 they called church socials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Many people divide society into different social classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In the time prior to 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and others to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh they did. Yes, you see, in our time - t
he doctor was the doctor. - And you looked up them. And the minister and was a minister and you thought they were ever so different to you. And a 1 a - the tradespeople, you - they thought they were it, and a solicitor. Buy now they don't you know do they
,
 they all mix more now but in that day - you sort of looked up to them you know a Vicar was a vicar, you know. You wouldn't say to a vicar, hello, and call him by his christian name, you know, you'd have to be right polite and - you know, same with our ow
n
 minister. Well now here they call him by the cirst name and all sorts. Ever so different you know, it's ever so different. But we were taught, you know, to look up to those, you know. A schoolteacher was looked up to. You know. But they're not as - not -
 
they don't bother now. You wouldn't say hello in street to a - to your teacher. You'd have a to - a boy would have to just touch his cap and - but you'll not - not see that now. It's very different. Different altogether. So there was that - there was a - 
there was a lot of class distinction. From a working man to a - a professional man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How many different categories would you say there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh well - I would say. I've seen a few snobs and I've seen 'em come down and all since. I've seen a few t
hings and - when you look back you just think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say you've seen somebody come down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Come down in their status, you know, and they thought they were going to be it for ever and ever and they haven't always. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Is this somebody particular you're thinking of now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, quite a few, I've had quite a few instances. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they thought they were it you see and - and because your father was a working man well - you weren't anything like. Then
 you come - grow up in life when you get married and your status goes up a lot and you just look back at it and you think - well - things work round don't they. But - there isn't that now. There isn't that distinction now. I mean, you don't get it. I mean
,
 everybody says hello now don't they. I mean - if you have a slocitor now he - I mean - well you - you're not awestruck now where we used to be in our days if it was solicitor. Oh goodness, we thought he was just - or a vicar or - you know. It - it - life
's very different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Which class would you say that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 My family. My father was a working man. Working class. But we were well brought up all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same class as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We
ll any working man didn't he. Any railwayman or collieryman or - and then there comes the - the professional men don't they. The thought sometimes they were a - a lot above you you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You were taught to treat some people differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Look up to them. Yes. You were taught that way, well you - somehow you did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there anybody that you had to curtsey to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there anybody that you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. No. Well we didn't mix with anybody like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, a lot of folks did, they thought the world of them. They was well respected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say your mother sort of married beneath her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, she did, yes, and her sister -
 her sister never forgive her you know. And she went - went right through life - well, I think that's rotten don't you. And - me mother and dad fell in love with each other at a dance, you know, and - they never wanted her to have him you know, but she - 
she did. And her dad - be liked - they were all right but they were poor. But - very refined me mother was. And we had to be - we were well brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But your mother's parents didn't bear any grudge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well she hadn't a father, he died you see. A
nd me mother was only fifteen when he died and - and she were just left with her mother, well - she got going out a bit you see and mixing with a different lot of girls you know and - you see, she had to go out to work. Well - my - her - her sister didn't
.
 She went to school 'til she was about sixteen and in that day it was a lot and then she never did go to work, she was at home and then got married and married a - a funeral director, a big - a big business man. Well my mother was left a child at fifteen 
w
ith just her mother and they lived together, they had to go into a small cottage and me mother had to go out to work and she worked for a tailoring you see. Well she mixed with a different lot of girls then and they used to go to these little dances in Wa
k
efield at the church and me dad used to go, boys from Normanton you know. They were only young. And that's how they met. And of course they didn't - they thought it was terrible, her sister did you see. But she'd been - she'd had the right end of the stic
k and mother got the wrong end of stick. She didn't mix with the same class you see then. And that's where class distinction comes you see. Mother got with a different \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 of girls. They do you know. More so in those days. But me mother and dad were very happy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say your mother's parents were business people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, in Wakefield. Drapers.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of people would they normally associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they had - with business people. Well there was a big jewelers shop, Perkins a
nd - a right lot of big shops in Walkefield and they were all big friends. Well my mother was out of all that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about the clergy, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Methodists, they were Methodists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who would the clergy mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I don't know I'm sure, don't remember. No. But Miss - me - me aunt, me mother's sister, she turned Aglican, she married an Anglican.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they just seemed to associate with their own lot you know and then with tradespeople, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would there be any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not much. No. Was industry - it was - the railway and mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about employers, were there any employers living in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Very good. Yes. And one that belonged the colliery were good. Nice people they were Catholics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well their own. They all kent their own - more or less their own - their own clique. But you see, my mother and dad kept very qu
iet because they hadn't the money to do it so - me mother wouldn't mix when she wouldn't mix with right class of people she wouldn't - she just kent quite \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Distinguishing between the church and the chapel, what sort of people would you say went to each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - the chapel people were more friendly you know, more - and the church people were more - well, they used to call 'em more nobby you know. The tradesfolks and - doctors and - professional people. People with more money. Yes. It se
emed very varied in those days. Well before - this war that came altered all that. It altered it all. But the war altered all that. That 1914. It wanted something to - was a lot of snobbishness. Well of course there still is isn't there really. But not as
 much as - as - as - as there used to be, there's not as much of that as there used to be now, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you say that were you lived all the people in the working class had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they were a bit different. There was so
me very - well - there were some very common people, which - me mother wouldn't mix with at all, you know. Not that she was snobbish but - she wouldn't like to be snob - but she had a mind of her own, you know, and she wouldn't let us mix you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of people do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Rough. Very rough. And rude. She used to call 'em rude. And the children were rude, you know. You know, not brought - not brought up as we were brought up. Even though me mother and dad was working - people. They made the best of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there a particular family that you knew that you would describe as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Yes. Very rough. Next door. Right rude and cheeky you know. Used to get on me mother's neves, I can hear her now going on. You don't play with them
, she used to say. And then they used to say me mother was snobbish you see. 'Cos she was very smart you know. Yes. She was rather bonny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 This family next door, what did it consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh they'd about seven youngsters you know and - and he was o
n the railway, the same as me - the same job as me dad did. But of course with seven - and he - they used to run in and run out, no meal - no - organization. No - you know, my mother - was always had a tablecloth on, table dressed, you know, but he - you 
k
now properly. If it were only bread and butter, it was set. But they used to go in just - you know - great big chunk of bread and - clear off. You see - now do you see what I mean. We'd only have the same thing, bread and jam, but it had to be to table. T
h
ere were no running round. With bread in your hand, we weren't allowed to do it. And you think about it after and used to - can't we have a bit of bread to go out? We used to say Charlie Mill and Clara Mill they're playing out with bread in their hand, ca
n
't we? You're not going out playing like that, you know, and I used to think sometimes, it'd be lovely to go out with a lump of bread in me hand. But I don't now you know, I - you think of it after don't you. But we weren't even allowed to do that you kno
w. And they thought me mother was stuck up you see because - we had to sit to table and have our meal, then go. Then go to us hearts conteny but no bread in your hand, no. No. Because they can be good mannered if they've not much money can't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember a distinction being felt between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. I do. I can remember that. Yes, I can. It was very very marked in those days, very much maked. A bos was a boss you know. A craftsman was a craftsman, you know. A teacher was
 a teacher, and you looked up to them you know. And I'll tell you what there was a lot of - too. That me mother and dad was heartbroke over. The scholarship - business. You sat for your scholarship in them days at ten. Well - I was poorly, I was off schoo
l
 a long time, I didn't sit. But she sat. And she was the top girl in the school and she did right well. And - the girl that got the scholarship, she were bottom. A dance. But her father was a - a big not on the council. And my - they had to put what their
 
father did. And - she had to put what her father did. Well she didn't get the scholarships. And they didn't then. There was the class distinction in our day. And we knew who was on the governors - well we thought - we knew after, but we didn't at the time
.
 And me mother was heartbroke. But she should have had that scholarship. And the - the headmaster did all in his power. Oh he was furious. 'Cos he knew, but he hadn't a say in it. And it - the governing body - they were - they were the - the people in the
 
town you know, they was somebody. Oh but this girl must go. She's so and so's daughter. And it was done every year that scholarship business. You know, when they used to get scholarships, to go to the High School. Eleven polus now but it was then ten. And
 
- and she never got her scholarship, she couldn't go. And of course they couldn't afford to pay for her to go. And these people could have acforded to pay for their daughter to have gone, you know, there was so many free scholarships then. And - and you s
e
e, to be a teacher - the teaching profession ten was looked up to very much you know. It would have been - and they were going to sacrifice to let her go in for teaching. Me mother and dad was. But they - they must go to the High School you see. You know,
 
Normanton had a High School. That - it was just a new one. Well if they couldn't go to receive - if they couldn't - if you didn't get to that High School they couldn't go into teaching. And - that was - that was one big class distinction and it was the go
verning body, that - that used to do - it was time that was altered. It was altered. And that was in our day. That - that's what used to happen. It was what your parents did, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
They - I never heard them say anything about anybody. I - the only time I - I have seen me dad so cross and go aff at the deep end was - over this scholarship - business. And then he said, I've never relt it as much in all my life, and
 that's what they're doing at working men. You know. When they take it out of your children, he didn't bother while we were little for himself, but when they take it out of your - your children - and they did in that day. You see. If your father wasn't so
rt of - they didn't get the scholarship. And I do know they for truth. Of course I didn't go in for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother and father - do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes I do. She went to a private school. You can tell how she'd feel can't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 She'd feel it because of her own background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
She - she'd had a good education. You cold tell she'd had one. But her parents paid for her, she went to a - a lady's school, a private school. And t
hat was a big thing in her day. She went to what they call Miss Lees school in Wakefield. And then she had to come down because she had to go out to work. But through circumstances - then you can't - then she meet - you see, our life. Turns doesn't it. Th
en - she mixed with a different class of folk then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 It was in Normanton - the - the - the fellow that started the Adult
 School, Mr Blakely wasn't it. Mr Blakely was a gentleman. He was. You could look up to him. And his son. Started the Adult School. For such men as me dad, you know, he had the money and he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We used to think world of him, bobby. Policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your home was rented from the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did you feel about the railway authority as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Not much. Me dad left. He went to the colliery. But doing the same work, and he was a lot happier. Then there came the slump you see and there was - a lot out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you said you didn't think much of the railway as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well, you see, never could get no promotion you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh - oh all right. All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel that your parents really had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh they did. When yo
u look back they did. You don't realize it at the time. But - I used to say - why don't you go to chapel with us mother? At Sunday night when we got a little bit bigger. Well, she said, I'll stop at home with your dad, he's been this morning to the Adult 
S
chool. Though I found out after why. Because she hadn't the collection. She used to give it us to take. And then she couldn't acford for - but we didn't know that. Not - you don't realize - it never dawned on us. But it did after. And she wouldn't go when
 she couldn't put anything in. You - you know, people don't realize do they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What difference did it make when your father was out of work during the slump?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh alwful. 'Cos they had to - manage best way they could you know. But of course she was w
orking you see and I was working. Like - and we helped them all we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Before you started school did you have any lessons from your parents or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, only - me mother was pretty good, she was a big reader and she used to read a lot to u
s you know. You know, good books. I remember sitting down - and - and she would - used to read a lot to us. And - we just went to an ordinary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How old were you when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Three, they used to send them at three. In't it fully.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What time in the morning did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Twelve, and then - one 'til four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You went all day when you started did you at three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, went home for lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say it was an ordinary school, do you mean it was a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
A - they called them a board school. We didn't go to the church of England school, and that school, I was born in 1890 and it was just opened in 1890. where it was free schooling, you hadn't to take a pen
ny you know. Used to take a penny a week I've heard me dad say. But it was free. I was just from that year. 1890, when free schooling - with the board schools, you know. Central Board School they called it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 It used to take us about quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - mother used to take us so far and then we used to meet the teacher that lived not - you know, no
t far away, and she used to take us along. But mind when I was only three we lived near the school. I was five I think when we went into this t'other house, you know, where I told you. The railway house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So your mother took you and then you met the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did that carry on all the time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Until we got - tom - old enough you know. 'Til I got about seven and then - we used to go with the other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You sent home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well, I liked it, I - I was - I liked it very well, and I can go back and I can remember - ever so well - the infants, you know, where we used to be taught to just set the tables, you know. You know, knife and fork and little cups and saucer. Like more 
of a play school. Until we got about five. I can remember them bits. All them bits. And then - I was very sharp at school but - when I was ten I had a breakdown, I never went anymore. I never went to school after I was ten. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say you liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And you remember the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Then I went into the big school and I got just under seven. I was sharp, too sharp we'll say. The doctor said so. I'd done so much and then I had a breakdown. I never went anymore. Wouldn't let me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You liked them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. I liked it, I liked school, I was very happy at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, they - very go
od at schoolmaster and he was very good on manners and very good on scripture. I always remember that. You know, the opening session. And then - then we - learned the - the best thing I was - most good at was sewing, I loved sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they emphasise things like tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. It was a good school. You see it would be new wouldn't it if it were only built in 1890. When I was born you see still going. Still a good school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they bother about the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Speech. Yes. But you did a lot of what - what did they used to call it - parsing and analyzing and - different method you know to what - altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You got the cane. Or you had to go stand in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of offences would merit the different sorts of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Talking. Talking and chattering and - misbehaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 If you were talking and suchlike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, giggling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you get the cane or would you be stood in the corner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - it just depended like - if you'd upset the whole class you know - you'd get the cane. If not, you'd to stand at front of the class you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did girls get the same punishments as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there much punishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. No. Very happy school. I had happy schooldays, what I can remember of ten. But you see it was so short. We went too early. I think - I think five's early enough. But used to go at three then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. We used to go home you know and show them stuff. It was a fairly - it was a fairly good - school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, but not luch as they do now. They didn't have these parent teachers days like they do now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 On what sort of occasions would they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - I think at the - well they call it end of term now don't they. Holidays you know. In the holidays to have a look at your work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Your parents met your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Not - not - as much as they're doing now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents go to the school to meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Or did they meet in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. And they only went if there was anything - they wanted to ask you know. Wasn't a regular - wasn't a teach - parent teachers association. I think we've advanced in that a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did the other children come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well some of them was a lot better off. Tradespeople, professional people. And some of them was - well, they couldn't have been much poorer because my dad didn't get much, but you see they'd homes where the parents drunk you see. Then th
e kids got now much. It's a mining area. In - in those days they used to go to the pubs a lot. Rather on the rough - type you know. You got those children and dirty children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did the teachers single out some children cor different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. I used to think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - they used to - we used to say get their knife into them a bit don't they. Couldn't bear 'em, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What particular children would these be, any particular type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, rougher type you know. They could tell when they come from a rougher home you know. And you'll always get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you mean that the teachers tried to discipline them more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Try to learn them manners you see. If they aren't taught manners at home it's hard at school in't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Some you were terrified of - at playtime. They'd gang up together, it's always been done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would this be boys or boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Boys and girls. It was a mixed school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - I - I should say so - there - there's be some. There would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well they weren't popular you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Any particular type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, well there'd be - very rough. You didn't want to mix them, isn't it funny, little as you are you know that it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there much mixing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But I made a friend - well she came to see me a fortnight ago - and we went to school together right from three year o
ld. We're still friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there much mixing between say people from your sort of home background and the better off ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You mixed quite freely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. There wasn't any particular snobbery. The only snobbery that came into it was when it got to - this scholarship business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But as far as the children themselves were concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. We were very friendly. In fact we contact yet a lot of 'em, them that's lying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You left school when you were ten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I left school at ten, yes. I never went any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You'd gone out of the infants into the juniors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Because - they didn't call it juniors then they called it the big school you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you find that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I liked it. Yes. Oh I liked school - what bit I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it the same sort of environment as the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Yes, and I can remember the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, ever so well. Yes. Oh I liked school. It was just that - I was ill you know. I broke down and hadn't to - come anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you have stayed longer if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Like me sister you see, she went 'tol she was - nearly fifteen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you attend any part time classes later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No. I hadn't to. I hadn't to do anything at all that was schooling. So that - I was - I - I - when I got better I'd be about thirteen. I used to go to the - taking babies out a bit. You know. Until I got fourteen. And then - I was put to dressmaking you
 see. Apprenticed. 'Cos that seemed to be me idea. I was a sew-er. Was a good job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you have any regrets about your education, finishing as it did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I often think - but it's rather strange I've got through. You know, I often - my husband o
ften used to say - well, you know, 'cos he was clever, he often used to say - you know, you can beat me in a lot of things, wit and - and he'd come and tell me you know. And - when Derek was - at Grammar school, he'd come home with his homework and I coul
d help him with comprehension, quick on the uptake, it's a good job isn't it. Nobody's ever known I've got through like that you know without an education really. The - the bit I got must have been good grounding. And then I've read a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you think you benefited from the ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Reading.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 From the time you did attend school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, definitely, because that's all the schooling I've had. And yet I've done right well. Did right well in business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You did a lot of reading for self education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 YES I did. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - good books you know that I could get from the library and that. I've always been a reader. Was then. Yes. I think it helps. And then mixing. Going into business you see. Sewing and meeting peop
le. I think that's a good education. Mixing. Taking part in things. You see, I - I'd rather nice voice, I could - in choirs and sing you know and then amateurs I went in. To say for a - a little village, we - mine place - we - oh we were very happy, we di
d very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Before you actually took up your apprenticeship at fourteen you sometimes used to take babies out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I did. Nursemaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any means of earning a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I got a bit for that. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you do anything else besides that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, no. No. I wasn't well enough. But pushing babies out, it was - two lots of different people who were in business you know. I was a nursemaid we'll say, ay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you do anything for the babies at home or just take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Play with them, that's all. Yes. I didn't go on for it, I didn't want to be a nursemaid, but it just - the doctor said it was the best thing I could do because it got me out. Used to go to the park and feed the ducks, you know, and - until you
 see, you couldn't go to your apprentice by law then until you were fourteen. And mother had got me name down you see to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where was it you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I went to a private - dressmaker. And she had three more hands you see. And then you had to se
rve - well had to do two years for nothing you know. Apprentice. Then when you're sixteen you're improver. And I went to one of the shops.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In your first job, in your apprenticeship, what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - you know - all the tacking and all the - picking pins up, mjg about like. 'Til you got onto a machine you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did they actually teach you how to do things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. I got on very quick. 'Cos you see I liked sewing. I think you've got to like a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who was responsible for training you there, was it the lady who had it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The lady, it was a private house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We used to go at half past eight in the morning and finish at - eight at night. And if we were 
buys we - were earlier, sometimes it were ten at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
We used to work on a Saturday morning. Unless we didn't get finished and then we had to work. There wasn't so much - like half days and all them sort of things in them days. They were long hours really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you went at half past eight you'd have a meal break at the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, no lunch. We just had lunch - dinner. About twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you go home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
An hour. And then we used to take our tea. 'cos we only had half an hour at tea time. Then we used to have it in the workroom you know. And then you finished when you finished, it depend how - in summer if it were Whitsuntide - well it'd be eight
 and then - ten o'clock. There wasn't any strict hours you know. That came into force later. Oh we used to work terribly long hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any holidays at all while you were apprenticed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A week. One week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You weren't paid at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no, not for two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother have to pay for you to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you get on with the other people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh - all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 All right. She was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I liked it, yes. Oh I picked it up very quick. Hadn't been there long before I had to start and make our own things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 After your two years apprenticeship you then went to this shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, to - what they call an improver. And got half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you working the same sort of hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. There was about sixteen of us. And the head - what they call the head dressmaker and a head improver, you know, you worked your way 
up. It was done a lot in them days where there isn't now is there, it's all - it's all ready made nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When you got into this job and were being paid when you had any holidays did they pay you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No pay for holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What holidays did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 A week. Still a week. We had to take it in our turn you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel that this half crown a week was a fair wage or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well in that day, yes. Then you had to go somewhere else and better yourself you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. And - all of it. Used to get about threepence - back. Funny in't it how we made do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What was it spent on, did it go in the family budget?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I - that helped to keep us. Wasn't much was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you find working at this place with more people, how did you get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh very well. Were happy time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What was the employer like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was this a woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. The man - it was a man that owned the shop. It was
 a big - it was a drapers shop you know. Used to do it you know a lot in those days. A workroom up above you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did the man who owned treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well he never saw us much. No. You see, the head dressmaker had the run of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And she was strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Ooh she was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh all right - I was allright.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You didn't find it too strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. You - you got used to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you feel about the work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 All right. I improved a lot there. Yes I did very well there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I stayed there - this one shop for a long time. And then - I went to other shop which was just a bit better and I got a bit more money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it as big?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Bigger. I got on a bit better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What were the conditions like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh good. All right. Her father was the chief of the - the inspector of police at Normanton, the head dressmaker. She was terribly strict, I - I give - I got on a lot better there. Yes. I
 stayed there 'til I was about - twenty. And then - I got a better job, I went to Castleford. To a high clays dressmaker. You know, better class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you get more money at this other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not - not a lot, you see - but got a lot more experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about when you got to Castleford to the high class place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes, I - I don't know - just a bit more, not much. But I went for experience you see. 'Cos they were the very - oh there's some beautiful things. She had all the better class you know. Different type you know altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you meet any of the customers there,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Not often, no. No. Nobody would do any fitting. No. I didn't like there I wasn't happy there. No. She were a bit too - strict. But I - I wanted to stick it because I was gaining a bit of experience you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you find the other people who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh there - they were - the - the second hands - they used to call them the second hand then, she was awfully good to us. And you see, you - you'd ha
ve a big - dressmaking establishment, you - you was a sleeve hand for a bit and you did nothing but sleeves. And they were those puffed sleeves you know, used to take some doing and all rushed. Then you got on a bit and you did - a skirt you see. With all
 piping. Oh I've - we used to do some beautiful clothes. Evening clothes you know. And - just them crepe de chine was all coming in. You know, crepe de chine, you'll have heard of it. Silk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you engaged on doing just a particular part of an article?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 YES? that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 All the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 All the time. You see, you came on and got on a bit further and I wanted to - to do it right through. And then the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How had it been at the other placez?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - you did a bit of everything. That was going. But you got a good grounding you know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you get a better grounding at this other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh my word, yes. Yes. Yes. You saw - you saw - you did a different type altogether. Different type of customers. It was a high class pla
ce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
I stayed about twelve months I think. And then I couldn't stick it any longer. Ooh 'cos she was strict. And I used to love coming back home, so I said - so I thought - and all at once I said - to me mother I said
, well aren't we silly. She says, how do you mean? I said, well going out working for this bit - I think I'm going to set up for myself. And - and me mother said, well you can have one of the bedrooms, we had three. And - I did do. Started me own workroom
. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 On your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
On my own. Yes. I thought it were time I were doing a bit - bit better 'cos I was going on for twenty-one, you know. And - I started with one apprentice. Then I got another one you know. Then I got three and a - and then I go
t an improver. I did right well. Had a good business. On me own. And I earnt a bit then. The first time. You know, getting - you - you know, when I - and I got some pretty good class trade in Normanton. You know, wedding orders and things like that. Right
 good orders, yes. I did that right up 'til the war you know, right up to - after I was married you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you find it, employing other people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I liked it. Yes. Oh and I got on very well with them. I've some lovely pictures - photo
graphs, where we're all taken together you know. Yes, I keep in touch now with some of them. Of course they're married and - yes. Oh we'd a very happy time. And me mother enjoyed it. Yes, she did. You see, 'cos she did all the door answering and all the -
 shopping for me. And all the - she used to do all me buttonholes and all because she'd learnt tailoring. And - and you know she was right happy with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So how long would you have this business then, what dates would it run from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I had it fr
om about - well I'd be about twenty. Let's see, Walter and I were engaged - he were twenty-two nearly I think. And then came the war you see. And of course I went on with it you see, we got married in 1915. And - and - and - I gave me business up about 19
17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So you'd have it from about 1910 to 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Some - yes. In the war, middle of the war years. I had the business. And then - but after I gave up the business - I gave it up because he broke down in the Army and I went to live with him you s
ee, so - the girls were carrying on but we got too much you see, I couldn't keep going to him and so I got some rooms and I stayed near him. And - and gave me business up and used to take a bit of sewing, anybody special that wanted anything, to where I l
ived you know, in the Army. And of course I never had - when he came home he wouldn't let me go on with me business. But I used to make odd dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So did you not have another job again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. I didn't start again, no. In our days you k
now they didn't - men didn't like their wives working. But I could earn a bit you know if I made one dress. If I made one dress a week. You know on my own. And me own I've always made me own clothes. I made them right up to this year. Well I could see but
 - I've got that I can't see as well and me daughter-in-law is gone to night school so - between us she'll run me 'em up now and I'll finish them of you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You feel that dressmaking was the right job for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you have preferred any other job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. No. No. I loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you belong to any union or organisation or trade association or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no, we didn't then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same outlook about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - I don't think there was - there wasn't - kind of unions then, there weren't while I was on me - in me own business the workroom act came in. And I had to have it up a big sheet you know how many square - you know and - and how many I empl
oyed and the man came, you know. See if the room was big enough. That all came in while I was - in business on me own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did it affect you in any way really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. I never used to let things bother me. No. I was fairly placid you see, good job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You didn't feel that your attitude to your job changed any when you started having your own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
No, I liked it. But of course you got that responsibility when it's your own. But you've a bit more in your pocket. You're working all those hours
 afen't you for - other people, I thought it were time I were doing a bit of something or else I would never going to get anything. 'Cos I - the long - the biggest wage I ever got, even at this posh big place, was eight shillings a week. Well it's not muc
h is it. When you're twenty. You're never going to save anything are you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What would your sort of net income be when you had your own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I should make - I should say - well - me husband used to do me books love but - I should say I made
 between three and four pound clear you know. And that was a fair lot in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. There was, and there was some girls - that could upset a whole workroom you know. I 
mean, when I worked at the shop. I hadn't any trouble. Mine were very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You found it did exist in some of the places you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I found out that - I - I'd seen so much in experience that I thought, if ever I'm a boss, you know, on me own, 
I'll win the girls and - you know, and any of them would do anything for me. Not - oh not put fear into them like she did at Castleford. I was terrified to death of her. And I remember me dad saying one night when I went home, well you don't go there no m
ore. He says, we'll starve first. He'd never seen me as miserable, you know. And I'd always been happy. But she was a terror. You'd a job to do anything right. Well if they don't win a girl I don't think they - they get them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you feel that there was a big division between the trained craftsman and the others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. There is. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In your line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. I think they want - you see - same as now, the night school training, it's all wrong, it's - Mary goes - but - I don't think
 it's a patch in learning properly. Because they don't get the grounding that we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 They're only really doing home dressmaking aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Thats all. But they have to have it cut out for them - where I could cut out, mearure, without a patter
n, you know. You know, plan and - you learn form the very - bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would you say that stating full time work changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, it is. You grow up all at once. Been tied down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You did continue to live at home when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, well I never went anywhere else I didn't. I was always at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well she was in an office you see, different work altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 But was your relationship with her altered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you spend your Sundays any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. We went to Sunday school and church and - they were - in them days that s what you did. You see, a small pl
ace. And then there was something every night in the week really. You know, you see, choir practice, amateurs - choral society. I loved that. You completed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You've told me a bit about how you spent your evenings when we were talking about when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. When I was young. Well I had nothing else to do in these small places.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you make any new friends about that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes, quite a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, we'd open house, 
me mother was good and dad. We've had some happy hours, we were talking about it when me friend was here the other week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you meet your new friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 At work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, this lady that came you know, she was my - well we did all us courting together and I was bridesmaid for her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You had boyfriends as well as girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh plenty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of places would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - it was church socials, t
hese dances at church. And now and again - oh Wakefield we used to go to - to - you know, to the Empire and - and then in Normanton we had pictures. And we used to go every Saturday night - to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - up to a point. But we had to be in at nine at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Even when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Even when we were working, yes. Yes, they were all - all very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about when you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I had to
 be - we hadn't that about it, I said it's home when I got in, a man, you know. But we used to go - we used to go in home, he used to go in you see. But - me dad used to say, what is there trailing about you see outside. Without we'd gone to a dance. We u
sed to go to some nice dances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You were married in 1915, how long had you know your husband?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh I'd known him all me life, like he was a Nomanton boy but - we started counting - in 1912. 1912. And so we'd do that a couple of years before the war
 you see. And he was in an office you know. Colliery office. Well - we used to - then the war broke out, 1914, I'll never forget that, we were at a wedding. And - he says, war's broken out, we didn't get papers much then. And it was Bank Holiday Monday. I
 
never forgot it. I said, a war? You know. Then papers started coming out, special - that's all how we got to know really. You know, we didn't know a right lot about it. It seemed to come right from sudden upon you, and do you know, life changed altogether
.
 Never been the same since. It was like a new era, you know. Before the 1914 war and after, nothing was the same and nobody was. It seemed to be a right alteration in everything. Upset everything. And then my husband joined up in 1914. You know, they expe
cted him to do. Long before the - conscription, then they had conscription. But he joinedup in 1914. Before -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you meet originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did we - oh well - we were going up and down in the town and that you know, and always - we'd always known one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And then the war rather interrupted your courting then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well he went away you see. 1914. He didn't go far away. He was posted at Pontefract. Because he wasn't very strong. And he was posted in Pontefract for a while, for - right up - we were married while he was at Pontefract. In 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you able to save up before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We were saving up very well, we were doing very well but of course that put us back a bit. But I was earning you see, I was doing all rig
ht with me business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your parents help you in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, they did what they could. And his parents - we did best we could. We had to do, it was a struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We were engaged in 1914. Easter 1914
. And then the war broke out you see and Bank Holidays, was a - a momentous year. And then he - he went away and then - I went on with the business and he used to come home when he could. And - and when we were married he was married in khaki.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You had the wedding reception at the Adult school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember much about the wedding itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. We'd a lovely wedding. Yes. But I wouldn't have while. I'd made that many wedding orders, you know. I made some gorgeous dres
ses. But I were that disgusted 'cos he were in this - I called it mucky old khaki. And - I a-id. I'm not having no white nor veil. 'Cos they wouldn't allow them to wear their civvies. Clothes. I said, no, and so I had a nice suit a navy blue - suit. Me fr
iend made it. Her who came the other week. It was lovely, and a big white hat. And flowers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Who was there at the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Both families you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there friends as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, the church was packed, choir and all thelot. We
'd a lovely wedding. But they expected to see bride in white and a veil and I wouldn't. I - I absolutely shocked all of them. Often thought about it after, 'cos they used to say, oh you'd have made a bonny bride. I says, I were all right as I was, I says,
 I - it didn't match up to that khaki stuff, I wouldn't no, if they'd have allowed him to have gone in his suit I would have done. But - the rest of the men were all in kaki you see. Spoilt the wedding. 'Cos you were rations you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you manage for the reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh - it was a struggle. But it was a lovely wedding. We - we scrounged round and - we did all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your mother do the catering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. We had somebody. One of the bakers you know. She did some of it you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have to provide the food because of the rationing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Or did the caterers do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh she did so - she did bedt she could for us. And then mother did a bit - we sckrounged round, Walters mother did a bit and - we've a lovely photograph of the wedding reception table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about wedding presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh we got a lot. YES? we'd a lovely wedding but - of course it were just married with the - war, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you able to have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. He only had tw
o days. We were married Christmas Day. Because you see, Christmas Day was on a Saturday. He came home at Friday night, we were married at Saturday and he'd to go back Monday morning. We didn't have us honeymoon for five years. He was away five years. We d
idn't set our home up for five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you continue to live with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 With me mother, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And then you took rooms near your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. No, we got a house when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Didn't you say you went into rooms for a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 We lived with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You moved into rooms so you could be near him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I did. Yes, down in - Withensea. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that not for very long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Oh about nine month. Because he broke down in training and - and - 
he was going to France you know and - and he couldn't - he wasn't fit. And then they put him - called C.3. you know, and then it's sedentary work and they put him in an office again. But he was down in Withensea. And so I got some rooms so I could go and 
have him out a bit to meals 'cos oh he was a wreck. They nearly finished him off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 So you didn't really start your married life properly for five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 After the war. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well when he came home you see we lived
 with me mother about - I say about - three or four months. That would be 1917 when it finished wouldn't it. No. 18.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he stay on 'til the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. 'Til he got demobbed. I think it was '18 - 1918 I think. It'd be 1918 - '15. Oh it would b
e '18 or '19 I've just forgotten. Anyway he came back to his work you know and - and we had a small house belonging the colliery. They did it up for us while we got one. And we was about ten months in it and - then we got a nice house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 In Normanton was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Yes. Yes. It's rather funny, I said to Derek I said, I start - we started married life in a cottage and I'm going to finish in a cottage. We'd a lovely little cottage - 'til we got a house you know. Belonging the - the colliery. You hadn't mo
ney to put down for - mortages then. And there wasn't so much buying houses. We got one to be rented you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How old was your husband when you married, about the same age as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I was twenty-five and he was twenty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You say he didn't like the idea of you doing any work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh he didn't. No. Wouldn't let me start the business again. I did a bit though. I used to do a bit at home. And one of the girls that used to work for me used to come up and help. She went out to work a bit
 and I said, ooh I'm get you some work. And - I could get sewing any time. And I got it for her sake really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How do you think that your husband felt about his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh he liked his work. He was clever he did well at his work. Was forty-four years there. He worked his way -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 At the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Yes, and while he came here you see, he was - he got to be colliery agent. You see, coming out. That's why we were here at Keighley.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did he like his work during the war do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well he didn't like being a soldier. But of course they - that was their duty and they - they had to do it. And of course when he - I was forty when we left Normanton. And forty years we've been here they was in 1914. You were content. But somehow or o
ther - everybody were grabbing and - you know, there seemed to be that spirit abroad. It upset the whole - show as they say. It woke us up I think. Life was different.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You hadn't really got a settled home in the first part of your marriage to prior to 1919 had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No, I went all over with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you know how much your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How much of it would he give to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh all of it but - but a big of pocket money, he didn't get big wages. No. 'Til after the war was over you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you discuss together how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Everything. Yes. Saved you know and - we had systematic saving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 During the period from your actual marriage up to the end of 1919 was there any one particular hou
se that you were at for a fairly settled period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Where would that he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Patrington down near Hull.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Is that a town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, it's a village. Near Withensea. You know, between Oldham and Withsnsey. Oh we were very happy there with some old people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 You were in rooms there were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did your accommodation consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Just one - oh accommodation - oh we lived with them but we'd a bedroom. A lovely bedroom but I lived with them and I paid so much a week. But Walter didn't have a thing to pay you see because he was in - at camp, which was
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your husband do any other jobs apart from being in the colliery office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh no. Went to night school. You see, when he came - when he got demobbed. He had to
 go back to night school you see to continue with his studies, because he was taking accountancy and all that you see. Well - it was really hard going for him. He'd to pull up again you see, to keep moving up with his office work, 'cos he wanted to get - 
o
n, you see and ready for next job that came available and he got what he wanted, he got to be a - an agent you see, where they go out you know. And then he would have gone back go have been a - the commercial manager, we'd have got - he'd have got to the 
top of the ree. And then that Labour government came in and they all became redundant. He came - he became redundant. When he was just sity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 The Labour government after the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 After Churchill. The one before. There's been - the Labour now 
and then there - there was the Conservatives. The first Labour that came in after the second world war. When they upset everything - nationalization, and the first thing they did was make such as my husband and all that had chief key jobs, redundant. And 
d
o you know, we didn't get a penny. Now - if any of the men on the colal board now become redundant they get a thousand pound. We got nothing. He just got three months notice. But he was just sixty. And he was just ready for his superannuation. And - he sa
i
d, I'll - I'll not tell you what he said, he said, I'll make them pay now. I'll go on it. And of course he'd be - he was on it all the time you see. And when theirs went up his had to go, they couldn't touch that. And he had a job in Keihley. Oh yes. He s
ays, I'll have to get a job 'til I'm sixty five - to keep - keep his - stamp, yes, his national - you know, to get the pension. And - and he got a little jog, a clerking job, but he was a come down you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was it a full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. But it
 were a shocking - I don't know how - I sometimes wonder how he faced it. Because he'd a right good job. First class pass all over, to Blackpool, Barreth and everything. But we never said much to anybody. And we kept this house going. We had his pension y
o
u see and then he got this little job and we managed. But it - oh talk about frustrating and disapprointing. It is - he'd had - forty-four years he'd worked there. You see, you work all your life. And that's what Labour did for us. Nationalisation's a ter
r
ible thing, it always makes me go cold when I hear about people being redundant. But they pay them money now. YES? So he hadn't much to do. And he'd plety on at his work. But he - as he said he never really caught up to that he missed during the ar. You k
n
ow, he went to night school for a long time you know. He were catching up that five years. And change you know, it was like a new era. Do you know, it was like a different world. You know. We often used to say that. We used to often say well things have n
e
ver been like about two miles away. We had a happy time there because they used to have some lovely camp - concerts you know. And the Sergeant Major and officers were - always good to him because he was such a clever - well clerk you see, he was clerking.
 In fact he could do job better than officers you know. We were very happy down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of a house was it that you lived at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh a lovely little house - cottage house you know. Down by the - well near the - what they call the sunk island
. I don't know whether you know that district or not, it's beautiful. May - you can get - you haven't far to go to Spurheard. Right in the country, oh I did like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What did the house consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well - a living room and a lounge and there were three bedrooms - no bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was there a separate kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Just a little small one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of arrangement did you have with the people you were with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I kept myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 And you used their kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. I kept mysel
f, I didn't board with them. I just paid eight shillings a week, you know, for the bedroom and - use of everything. And then I used to - keep myself. And him and all because they didn't get much at camp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did your husband ever come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh a lot. Every night. But - not to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he come for leaves there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No, we came home. To - to me mother's. Eeh I often think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you manage for washing and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh all right, there were a wash house outside. Oh
 we did very well, I was very comfortable. In fact we're friends with them yet, the granddaughter. You know, as the family's gone on. I - in fact Derek and Mary went for their honeymoon to Withensey, to Etties. And Etty was the granddaughter and so she wa
s only a little tiny child when we were there. Well we made very big frienss with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What was your daily routine while you were living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh - bored stiff sometimes. I always take a bit of sewing. And I'd go for walks. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about the housework part of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh I didn't trouble to do any housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
She was a lovely old lady. Oh no, no. Just me own washing up and - I kept me own bedroom clean. I had a lovely bedroom, a lovely view. I was very happy there. Longing for the day when war finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have much opportunity to experiment with your cooking and whatnot there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. No. No. No, she did it all herself. No. And it was all done - by the fire oven you know. You know. Range. But very happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Can you remember how you and your husband would spend Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Well - twice we down there, you know, we didn't always get leave. We just had to make best of it. And it was always our wedding day. All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you celebrate it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well just in a quiet way in country you know. All very quiet people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you do any reading much while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, I did. Did a lot of reading. But as I say I used to take some sewing. I did a lot od embroidery. I was always doing something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were there any books in the house there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Not much. No. I took them from home. Or bought them. Or anybody - or anybody'd give me. Or they used to get some at camp sometimes. NevThen they had camp concers you know. And
 - and we used to visit. I got very friendly with the Sergeant - and his wife. And believe me, I don't whether you do or not - I'd never seen face powder. They taught me how to use face powder. 'Cos she came from Hill, from a town you know. Often laugh ab
out it. You know, a compact. And me mother says, what's that stuff you're putting on your face? We'd never done all that like you know. Eeh we often laughed about it. But talk about wakeing up in a - after another - in another era. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you spend Saturdays and Sundays with your husband at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 When he could get out, they weren't much different. You didn't know one day from another, believe me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you spend your Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well I used to like to go to Hull Saturday.
 You know, to town. And I made a friend there. Through coming down to Withenseay. She used to come to - there was one bit I had - they - Walter was stationed at Withensey and I had six weeks with some right nice people. And I met this lady from Hull there
.
 She were a lovely person, she lived in a lovely house you know, well she used to ask me sometimes for weekend. Oh and I made some lovely contacts and wekept them up, right 'til they died. Oh we did very well, we made some - but I was a friendly person an
d I - I made friends you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What about your Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh there was a little chapel. Little village chapel. I used to go a bit. Well I used to go every Sunday. With the country people you know you don't get very close to them. They're very narro
w, terribly narrow. Awfully narrow, because when I used to come home and we used to say, we've had concerts, you know, you know dressing up at our Sunday school. Concerts, they said, never heard of such a thing in the chapel. That's old fashioned they wer
e. So I - I gave up telling them you know. Cos ours was - in Normanton I thought we were small enough but we - we were - we did have a bit of life you know. But these country places don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 How did you find the village community there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh terribly narrow. Terribly narrow. Before they accept you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 What sort of people was the community composed of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Well there were - farmers mainly you know, mainly farm. And fishermen you see, fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you have any views on social class there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 
Oh no, not like that, we got it at camp though. Got it at camp you know. There was all sorts there. You know, I got to know, soldiers wives you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Not much. If anything we were Liberals you k
now. My husband was a Conservative though. Big Conservative. Well we never fell out over - we never we never argued.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Do you remember voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 I don't think women had votes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 1918 was the first one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes, wen Pankhurst - you know, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did you vote that first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Oh yes. When I could do. Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Would your husband vote then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 He'd be in the Army wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. YES? THEY voted. But after I got married to him I voted with him, the same as him. Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Were you not very particular about which party you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Not politics - no. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did he persuade you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. He never bothered - he didn't bother. But he was a true b
lue you know but he didn't - he didn't do any - he says, I'll never getting into red about politics. But he said, I don't want to - I've owt to do with Labour - he wouldn't have out - any truck with - especially after what they did. Well of course we reme
m
ber Labour party just coming up. 'Cos it was Liberal remember. 'Cos when we were children at school - he went to church school, I can remember him, and I went to board school, well mainly that went to the board school, we used to have yellow ribbons. Libe
rals. And church you know, we used to call them church blue dogs, bulldogs. All had their blue ribbons, it - oh always used to sport us ribbons. 'Cos I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Did either you or your husband take part in any political activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 No. Never. No. No, we just pay us clubs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Was that for the club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes. Membership. I was on the committee for - for - once, here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid397911 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 That's recent though is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16257840 LL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9927555\charrsid3476281 Yes.
\par }}